-- Spain 10-Year Yield Rises to 6.5%, Biggest Increase in a Month
-- B y   E m m a   C h a r l t o n
-- 2012-06-11T15:18:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-11/spain-10-year-yield-rises-to-6-5-biggest-increase-in-a-month.html
Spain ’s government bonds slumped,
pushing the 10-year bond yield up 28 basis points to 6.50
percent at 4:16 p.m. London time. That’s the biggest intraday
gain since May 14.  Two-year Spanish note yields climbed 25 basis points to
4.53 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
